The beach terminates to the east where sand runs against a cliff which curves around from the north. An aged wooden stairway climbs the cliff, swaying precariously in the ever-present breeze. Only a careful or skilled climber will successfully navigate them to the top of the cliff. The ruins of a stone tower stand mournfully on the beach just above the rolling surf.
*DESCRIPTION_END
