NUMBER 556
NAME Eltinmar River, eastern side
PLAIN
DAY_LIGHT
CALL 33
ITEM 9 693
*DESCRIPTION_START
A narrow road comes out of some hills to the northeast and ends at the eastern bank of the Eltinmar River. The river is wide and deep, carrying its icy cold waters from the mountain range on a long, winding trip, finally depositing them into the Inner Sea. Abner McKneid and his sons engage in a brisk business of ferrying people across the river here.
*DESCRIPTION_END
*DESCRIPTION_START ITEM EXAM 2
It is a simple craft fashioned from logs strapped together with leather.
*DESCRIPTION_END
EXIT NE 554
EXIT ABOVE 2150
IFENTRY
	EQUAL EVENTEST TIM
	MOD EVENTEST 2
	IFVAR EVENTEST = 0
		IFITEM 1
			ECHO GROUP You notice that one of Abner's sons is waiting here with a raft. A gangplank leads on board.
		ENDIF
		IFNOITEM 1
;			ECHO ALL One of Abner's sons pilots the raft to the shore and puts down the gangplank.
			ECHO GROUP You notice that one of Abner's sons is waiting here with a raft. A gangplank leads on board.
			NEWITEM 1 412
			NEWITEM 2 403
		ENDIF
	ENDIF
	IFVAR EVENTEST ! 0
		ECHO ALL You notice there is no raft here to take you across at the moment.
		IFITEM 1
			REMOVEITEM 1
		ENDIF
		SETEVENT 1 40 ALWAYS
		CONTEVENT 1
		IFNOITEM 1
			NEWITEM 1 412
			NEWITEM 2 403
			ECHO ALL One of Abner's sons pilots the raft to the shore and puts down the gangplank.
		ENDIF
	ENDIF
ENDIF
IFVERB GO 1
	IFVAR INTNUM7 ! 1
		ECHO PLAYER One of Abner's sons stops you. "You must pay first! The fee is one shilling." he says.
		ECHO OTHERS %N tries to get on the raft without paying!
	ENDIF
	IFVAR INTNUM7 = 1
		ECHO PLAYER You walk up the gangplank and board Abner's raft.
		ECHO OTHERS %N walks up the gangplank and boards Abner's raft.
		MOVE 2015
		AFFECT 2015
		ECHO OTHERS %N boards the raft.
		AFFECT 556
	ENDIF
	CLEARVERB
ENDIF
IFVERB PAY -1
	IFVAR INTNUM7 = 1
		ECHO PLAYER Abner's son politely informs you that you do not need to pay again.
		ECHO OTHERS %N tries to give Abner's son a tip.
	ENDIF
	IFVAR INTNUM7 ! 1
		IFVAR WEALTH < 10
			ECHO PLAYER Abner's son looks none too patient as he taps his foot, waiting for you to come up with enough cash.
			ECHO OTHERS %N doesn't seem to be able to cough up the fare. Abner's son gives %i a dirty look and turns his attentions to better potential customers.
		ENDIF
		IFVAR WEALTH = 10
			SUB WEALTH 10
			ECHO PLAYER You hand over your last money to Abner's son.
			ECHO OTHERS %N hands Abner's son some coins.
			EQUAL INTNUM7 1
		ENDIF
		IFVAR WEALTH > 10
			SUB WEALTH 10
			ECHO PLAYER You fork over some money. Abner's son hands you back some change.
			ECHO OTHERS %N hands Abner's son some coins.
			EQUAL INTNUM7 1
		ENDIF
	ENDIF
	CLEARVERB
ENDIF
