A majestic bridge spans a gap between your ledge and another mountain just to the west. The ledge you are standing on continues around to the northeast and northwest.
*DESCRIPTION_END
MOUNTAIN
DAY_LIGHT
EXIT NE 633
EXIT NW 635
EXIT ABOVE 2108
;
NUMBER 637
NAME Teeth of Shartan, thinning mist
MONSTER_GROUP 54
CALL 33
ITEM 9 693
*DESCRIPTION_START
The mist on this side of the mountain is significantly thinner than the white blanket to the southwest. Under that cover you can make out the bridge. Its destination can't be determine from here.
*DESCRIPTION_END
MOUNTAIN
DAY_LIGHT
EXIT SW 632
EXIT E 638
EXIT ABOVE 2114
;
NUMBER 638
NAME Teeth of Shartan, canyon view
MONSTER_GROUP 54
CALL 33
ITEM 9 693
*DESCRIPTION_START
A recent rockslide has filled in a section of the slope below the widening mountain path, piling a trail of rocks and debris against the cliff. Far below, the wavering silver line of a stream threads through a rugged mountain canyon. The fog continues to dissipate to the southeast.
*DESCRIPTION_END
MOUNTAIN
DAY_LIGHT
EXIT W 637
EXIT SE 639
EXIT ABOVE 2115
ITEM 0 82 ADJ1=264  VAL2=700
; Item 0 is a rocky trail to room 700
;
*DESCRIPTION_START ITEM EXAM 0
It looks as if a large section of the mountain ledge has collapsed and slid
down the mountainside, allowing a cautious climb down into the valley below.
*DESCRIPTION_END
;
NUMBER 639
NAME Teeth of Shartan, rock wall
MONSTER_GROUP 54
CALL 33
ITEM 9 693
*DESCRIPTION_START
The ledge twists around the mountain and comes to an abrupt halt at a wall of rock. The only reasonable path is the ledge back. There is almost no fog here, and you may enjoy a clear view of the remaining range to the east, stretching out seemingly forever.
*DESCRIPTION_END
MOUNTAIN
DAY_LIGHT
EXIT NW 638
EXIT ABOVE 2115
;
NUMBER 640
NAME Teeth of Shartan, canyon view
CALL 33
ITEM 9 693
*DESCRIPTION_START
The ledge proceeds to the west. From here you can see down the side of the mountain toward a canyon. It begins in the northeast as a crevice between two neighboring peaks and expands into a valley nestled in the middle of the range. A trickle of water drips from a crevice providing a home for a colony of lichen.
*DESCRIPTION_END
MOUNTAIN
DAY_LIGHT
ITEM 0 63 VAL2=1749
IFVERB SEARCH -1
	IFVAR INTNUM25 = 1
		ECHO PLAYER You find the crevice Menelian spoke of.
	ENDIF
ENDIF
IFPREVERB GO 0
	IFVAR INTNUM25 ! 1
		IFVAR FLAG1 = 1
			DISBAND
			ECHO PLAYER Having observed closely, you follow into the crevice. The cramped crevice continues suffocatingly, hundreds of spans into the rock. Eventually, you exit into a cave...
			EQUAL GFLAG1 1
			EQUAL INTNUM25 1
			EQUAL ROUNDTIME 20
		ELSE
			ECHO PLAYER There are hundred of crevices here, but they all appear to dead-end after only a few feet.
			CLEARVERB
		ENDIF
	ELSE
		DISBAND
		ECHO PLAYER You find the proper crevice, and enter. The cramped crevice continues suffocatingly, hundreds of spans into the rock. Eventually, you exit into a cave...
		EQUAL GFLAG1 1
		EQUAL INTNUM25 1
		EQUAL ROUNDTIME 20
	ENDIF
ENDIF
