NUMBER 700
NAME Teeth of Shartan, Rocky Trail
CALL 33
ITEM 9 693
*DESCRIPTION_START
A wide section of the hillside has slumped downward here, cutting a trail
through the otherwise impassable mountain peaks. Little vegitation
is evident here, save a few trees which manage to survive here as stunted
dwarves which bear little resemblance to their greater cousins. A steep
slope leads down into a deep valley below.
*DESCRIPTION_END
MOUNTAIN
DAY_LIGHT
MONSTER_GROUP 28
EXIT D 701
EXIT ABOVE 4
;
ITEM 0 82 ADJ1=264  VAL2=638
;
;
NUMBER 701
NAME Teeth of Shartan, Scramble
CALL 33
ITEM 9 693
*DESCRIPTION_START
Bits of broken rock and other rubble from a recent slide have made
something of a path here, allowing careful travellers access to a rugged
valley through the mountains. The rocks are quite unstable, though, and
each step must be made with great care to avoid disaster.
*DESCRIPTION_END
MOUNTAIN
DAY_LIGHT
MONSTER_GROUP 28
EXIT D 746
EXIT U 700
IFENTRY
   RANDOM DUMMY1 1 10 0
   IFVAR DUMMY1 < 4
      ECHO PLAYER Oh no! You seemed to have taken a bad step...
      ECHO OTHERS %n slips on some loose rubble and slides down the hill.
      MOVE 746
      AFFECT 746
      ECHO PLAYER You slide down the loose rock and come to a halt.
      ECHO OTHERS %n comes sliding down the loose rock from above.
      POSITION LAY
      AFFECT 701
   ENDIF
ENDIF
;
NUMBER 746
NAME Teeth of Shartan, Streambed
CALL 33
ITEM 9 693
*DESCRIPTION_START
A frothing mountain stream surges down the mountains, rolling over the
rocks and debris in its bed with reckless abandon. Downstream from here,
the massive rock walls of the valley close tightly around the stream. To
the north, however, the valley widens somewhat. Countless eons of traffic
by all sorts of travellers have worn a fine trail which winds northward
through the the valley towards towering peaks. Another path of loose
rubble leads up the steep valley wall.
*DESCRIPTION_END
MOUNTAIN
DAY_LIGHT
MONSTER_GROUP 28
EXIT N 702
EXIT U 701
EXIT ABOVE 4
;
NUMBER 702
NAME Teeth of Shartan, Streambed
CALL 33
ITEM 9 693
*DESCRIPTION_START
A sheet of spray splashes over a worn outcrop of terraced bedrock here,
hissing like a gentle shower. Amidst the curtains of mist, a delicate clump
of white penetine blossoms cling to a mossy ledge. The path and the stream
meander down through the mountains to the south, and rise towards a great
gap in the massive peaks to the northeast.
*DESCRIPTION_END
MOUNTAIN
DAY_LIGHT
MONSTER_GROUP 28
EXIT ABOVE 4
EXIT S 746
EXIT NE 703
;
ITEM 0 275 ADJ1=347 ADJ2=576
; Item 0 is a white penetine blossom
*DESCRIPTION_START ITEM EXAM 0
The penetine blossoms are tiny but numerous flowers, each with five petals,
arranged in a perfect sphere.
*DESCRIPTION_END
;
IFVERB RECALL -1
  IFVAR skill32 > 0
    ECHO PLAYER Penetine blossoms, also known as the Tears of Shemri, are tiny clustered flowers found only in the wettest locations at altitudes well above sea level.
  ENDIF
  IFVAR skill32 > 4
    ECHO PLAYER According to legend, the Tears of Shemri were created where the goddess wept after her husband, Amilor, slew her first son, Shartan. The bitter Shemri gave the beautiful flower a lethal poison which affects the unfortunate admirer who stops to smell them.
  ENDIF
ENDIF
;
IFPREVERB smell 0
  CLEARVERB
  ECHO PLAYER The smell of the flowers is cloying and makes your stomach turn.
  ECHO OTHERS %N takes in the fragrance of the penetine blossoms.
  DAMAGEPLR POISON 8 A wave of dizziness leaves you weak.
ENDIF
;
IFPREVERB get 0
  CLEARVERB
  ECHO PLAYER The delicate blossoms crumble as you try to grasp them.
  ECHO OTHERS %n crushes some penetine blossoms in %h grasp.
ENDIF
;
IFPREVERB eat 0
  CLEARVERB
  ECHO PLAYER The taste of the blossoms is sickeningly sweet.
  ECHO OTHERS %N just ate some of the penetine blossoms.
  DAMAGEPLR POISON 12 They make you feel quite ill.
ENDIF
;
;
NUMBER 703
NAME Teeth of Shartan, Valley
CALL 33
ITEM 9 693
*DESCRIPTION_START
A slight turn in the stream's course has created a beach of polished stones
on this bank of the stream. On the opposite side, an undercut rock face
hangs ominously over the stream, threatening to drop at any moment. Several
large rocks in midstream are evidence that the stream has been cutting
into the cliff for some time.
*DESCRIPTION_END
OUTDOOR_OTHER
DAY_LIGHT
MONSTER_GROUP 28
EXIT SW 702
EXIT NE 704
EXIT ABOVE 4
;
;
NUMBER 704
NAME Teeth of Shartan, Valley
CALL 33
ITEM 9 693
*DESCRIPTION_START
Two great mountain peaks flank the valley on either side here, like the
towers of a titanic gatehouse. The enormity of the mountains makes the wide
valley seem tight and claustrophic despite its considerable width.
Occasional uquart trees dot the few flat spots along their steep slopes.
*DESCRIPTION_END
OUTDOOR_OTHER
DAY_LIGHT
MONSTER_GROUP 28
EXIT SW 703
EXIT N 705
EXIT ABOVE 4
;
IFVERB recall -1
   IFVAR skill32 > 2
      ECHO PLAYER Uquart trees are species of rough-barked fir found only in high, barren regions. They manage to thrive in climates where few other plants can survive.
   ENDIF
ENDIF
;
NUMBER 705
NAME Teeth of Shartan, Valley
CALL 33
ITEM 9 693
*DESCRIPTION_START
Several large boulders are strewn about the valley floor here, no doubt having rolled from the fractured peaks of the mountains above. Two particularly massive boulders have come to rest in midstream, channelling the flow of water between them into a roaring, frothing chute.
*DESCRIPTION_END
OUTDOOR_OTHER
DAY_LIGHT
MONSTER_GROUP 28
EXIT S 704
EXIT ABOVE 4
EXIT N 708
;
ITEM 0 78 ADJ1=189 VAL2=706
; Item 0 is a climbable boulder portal
;
NUMBER 706
NAME Teeth of Shartan, atop a boulder
CALL 33
ITEM 9 693
*DESCRIPTION_START
This large boulder stands partway out into the rapidly flowing waters of the mountian stream. A second boulder, nearly as large as this one, stands on the opposite bank of the stream. An agile person could probably jump across the stream here to the other boulder.
*DESCRIPTION_END
OUTDOOR_OTHER
DAY_LIGHT
EXIT ABOVE 4
EXIT D 705
;
; The following code allows the player to jump, with a skill check and roll,
; to the other boulder across the stream. The jump is fairly easy and all
; but the clumsiest will be able to cross. Failure simply results in the
; player not making an attempt.
;
ITEM 0 367
; non-portal boulder
EQUAL abflag 0
IFVERB jump 0
   CLEARVERB
   RANDOM abroll 1 100 0
   IFVAR abroll < 5
      EQUAL abflag 1
      ECHO PLAYER Before you can even attempt the jump, you loose your footing on the slippery wet rock and fall.
      ECHO OTHERS %n stumbles and falls while attempting to jump to the other boulder.
      POSITION LAY
   ENDIF
   IFVAR abflag ! 1
      EQUAL abag AGI
      ADD abroll abag
      IFVAR abroll < 70
         ECHO PLAYER You jump to the other side and arrive on the boulder with a solid and rather painful thump.
         ECHO OTHERS %n jumps across to the other boulder and falls against the rock with a solid thump.
         RANDOM abouch 1 25
         DAMAGE CRUSH 25 %n is injured by the impact.
         MOVE 707
         POSITION LAY
         AFFECT 707
         ECHO OTHERS %n jumps from the other boulder and lands with a solid thump.
         AFFECT 706
         EQUAL abflag 1
      ENDIF
      IFVAR abflag ! 1
         IFVAR abroll < 120
            ECHO PLAYER You successfully jump to the other boulder, but your feet slide out from under you as you land.
            ECHO OTHERS %n jumps to the other boulder but lands most indelicately on %h behind.
            MOVE 707
            POSITION SIT
            AFFECT 707
            ECHO OTHERS %N jumps to this boulder from the other but lands most indelicately on %h behind.
            AFFECT 706
            EQUAL abflag 1
         ENDIF
      ENDIF
      IFVAR abflag ! 1
         IFVAR abroll < 160
            ECHO PLAYER You successfully jump to the other boulder.
            ECHO OTHERS %n successfully jumps to the other boulder.
            MOVE 707
            AFFECT 707
            ECHO OTHERS %n successfully jumps from the other boulder to this one.
            AFFECT 706
            EQUAL abflag 1
         ENDIF
      ENDIF
      IFVAR abroll >= 160
         ECHO PLAYER You gracefully leap to the other boulder.
         ECHO OTHERS %n gracefully leaps to the other boulder.
         MOVE 707
         AFFECT 707
         ECHO OTHERS %n gracefully leaps from the other boulder to this one.
         AFFECT 706
      ENDIF
   ENDIF
ENDIF
;
IFTOUCH 0
   CLEARVERB
   ECHO PLAYER You can't reach the other boulder from here.
ENDIF
;
NUMBER 707
NAME Teeth of Shartan, Atop a boulder
CALL 33
ITEM 9 693
*DESCRIPTION_START
This large boulder stands partway out into the rapidly flowing waters of the
mountian stream. Another boulder, even larger than this one, stands on the
opposite bank of the stream. An agile person might be able to jump across the
stream here to the other boulder.
*DESCRIPTION_END
OUTDOOR_OTHER
DAY_LIGHT
EXIT ABOVE 4
EXIT D 731
;
ITEM 0 367
; non-portal boulder
EQUAL abflag2 0
IFVERB jump 0
   CLEARVERB
   RANDOM abroll2 1 100 0
   IFVAR abroll2 < 5
      EQUAL abflag2 1
      ECHO PLAYER Before you can even attempt the jump, you loose your footing on the slippery wet rock.
      ECHO OTHERS %n stumbles and falls while attempting to jump to the other boulder.
      POSITION LAY
   ENDIF
   IFVAR abflag2 ! 1
      EQUAL abag2 AGI
      ADD abroll2 abag2
      IFVAR abroll2 < 80
         ECHO PLAYER You jump to the other side and arrive on the boulder with a solid and rather painful thump.
         ECHO OTHERS %n jumps across to the other boulder and falls against the rock with a solid thump.
         RANDOM 1 25 abouch2
         DAMAGE CRUSH abouch %n is injured by the impact.
         MOVE 706
         POSITION LAY
         AFFECT 706
         ECHO OTHERS %n jumps from the other boulder and lands with a solid thump.
         AFFECT 707
         EQUAL abflag2 1
      ENDIF
      IFVAR abflag2 ! 1
         IFVAR abroll2 < 140
            ECHO PLAYER You successfully jump to the other boulder, but your feet slide out from under you as you land.
            ECHO OTHERS %n jumps to the other boulder but lands most indelicately on %h behind.
            MOVE 706
            POSITION SIT
            AFFECT 706
            ECHO OTHERS %N jumps to this boulder from the other but lands most indelicately on %h behind.
            AFFECT 707
            EQUAL abflag2 1
         ENDIF
      ENDIF
      IFVAR abflag2 ! 1
         IFVAR abroll2 < 180
            ECHO PLAYER You successfully jump to the other boulder.
            ECHO OTHERS %n successfully jumps to the other boulder.
            MOVE 706
            AFFECT 706
            ECHO OTHERS %n successfully jumps from the other boulder to this one.
            AFFECT 707
            EQUAL abflag2 1
         ENDIF
      ENDIF
      IFVAR abroll2 >= 180
         ECHO PLAYER You gracefully leap to the other boulder.
         ECHO OTHERS %n gracefully leaps to the other boulder.
         MOVE 706
         AFFECT 706
         ECHO OTHERS %n gracefully leaps from the other boulder to this one.
         AFFECT 707
      ENDIF
   ENDIF
ENDIF
;
