NUMBER 744
NAME Fang of Shartan, Summit
CALL 33
ITEM 9 693
*DESCRIPTION_START
From atop this lofty peak the entire valley below seems insignificant and
tiny. The roaring mountain stream is but a pale ribbon of silver, and even
the lake seems puny compared to the grandeur of the mountain. What seemed
a flattened, broken peak from below is now clearly something very different;
the top of the mountain is a ring of rock surrounding a wide, flat, barren
basin. In the center of the basin is a low stone structure. A steep trail
leads down through the rocks towards the middle of the basin, and narrow
crevice provides some minimal footing for the dangerous climb down the
mountain face.
*DESCRIPTION_END
DAY_LIGHT
EXIT D 944
